id: pm-z87r
title: 2026-04-26 Comprehensive PM CLI Dogfood Audit - Full Results
description: "Complete manual dogfood audit of the pm CLI covering core commands, SDK, extensions, calendar, telemetry, agent UX, and extensibility. Conducted in a temporary sandbox project exercising all command groups."
type: Decision
status: open
priority: 0
tags[5]: audit,decision,dogfood,"milestone:0",pm-cli
created_at: "2026-04-26T20:20:21.167Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-26T20:20:21.167Z"
author: audit-agent
body: "# PM CLI Dogfood Audit Results (2026-04-26)\\n\\n## Executive Summary\\nThe pm CLI is a mature, highly extensible project management tool. Core functionality is solid with 1064/1065 tests passing. The telemetry pipeline is fully operational. Calendar, extensions, and SDK are functional with specific improvement areas identified.\\n\\n## Test Results\\n- 78/79 test files pass\\n- 1064/1065 individual tests pass\\n- 1 test fixed during audit (health check assertion)\\n\\n## Areas Verified Working\\n1. Core CRUD lifecycle (all 6 item types)\\n2. Hierarchy (parent/child linking, deps tree)\\n3. Claim/release/start-task/pause-task/close-task workflow\\n4. Comments/notes/learnings append-style updates\\n5. File/doc/test linking\\n6. History with deterministic hash chains\\n7. Calendar (4 views x 3 formats)\\n8. Extensions (install/manage/doctor/activate)\\n9. Telemetry (9-container stack, E2E event flow)\\n10. Search (hybrid mode with fallback)\\n11. Aggregate, dedupe-audit, validate, health, stats\\n12. Config, governance presets\\n13. Completion (bash/zsh/fish)\\n14. Update-many with dry-run\\n15. Context command for agent triage\\n\\n## Issues Found (filed as pm items)\\n1. pm-hb6x: Integration test health check assertion missing telemetry (P0, fixed)\\n2. pm-bhhe: Aggregate group-by limited to parent|type only (P2)\\n3. Calendar --full-period rejected for agenda view (P2)\\n4. pm-6y6i: Templates command syntax unclear (P2)\\n5. pm-qrxb: SDK docs missing cli-contracts layer documentation (P1)\\n6. Update-many error message lacks guidance on available flags (P3)\\n\\n## Extensibility Assessment\\n- Extension API: 14 register methods + 5 hooks = comprehensive\\n- 9 capabilities: commands, renderers, hooks, schema, importers, search, parser, preflight, services\\n- SDK exports proper types for all extension interfaces\\n- Starter extension example exists\\n- Bundled extensions (beads, todos) work correctly\\n\\n## Agent UX Assessment\\n- TOON output is token-efficient and structured\\n- JSON output is machine-parseable\\n- Error messages follow consistent pattern with context\\n- Context command provides excellent triage snapshot\\n- Contracts command enables programmatic flag discovery\\n- Completion generation works for bash/zsh/fish\\n\\n## Telemetry Security\\n- .gitignore excludes runtime/telemetry/ and .env\\n- Sensitive data redaction in place (emails, tokens, passwords, paths)\\n- No hardcoded secrets in source\\n- Operations docs stored in gitignored .agents/pm/search/\\n\\n## Recommendations\\n1. Expand aggregate group-by fields for universal PM use\\n2. Document SDK cli-contracts layer\\n3. Add capability requirement docs to EXTENSIONS.md\\n4. Export ExtensionCommandArgumentDefinition from SDK\\n5. Add @deprecated on CommandDefinition.handler\\n6. Clarify templates command syntax"
